document_data.name: Farnath Ilistar II
document_data.mainbody: '''Farnath Ilistar II''' was the fifth King of the [[Ilistar Dynasty]] who ruled the city-state of [[Westgate]].
document_data.Activities: Farnath II reclaimed the throne of Westgate for his family when the [[cambion]] King [[Iyachtu Xvim]] was forced to flee the city by a [[mercenary]] host in the {{YearlinkName|734}}. He ruled until the {{YearlinkName|756}}.
document_data.Relationships: Farnath II was the great-great-grandson of King [[Farnath Ilistar I|Farnath I]]. He was descended from King [[Belhendar Ilistar|Belhendar's]] younger half-brother. His son and heir was the simpleton Prince [[Farnath Ilistar III|Farnath III]] and his younger brother was [[Temprith Ilistar|Temprith]].
